Explanation:

The solution uses a for loop to iterate from 1 to n. Inside the loop, it converts the integer to a string, splits it into an array of characters, sorts the array, and then converts the sorted array back to an integer and adds it to the result list. This ensures that the resulting list contains all numbers from 1 to n in lexicographical order. The algorithm runs in O(n) time complexity and uses O(1) space complexity, making it efficient for solving the problem.

